<P><SPAN class=t>Global Diversified Industries Launches Its New 
Website</SPAN><BR><SPAN class=tt>Thursday June 16, 5:00 am ET</SPAN> 
<TABLE height=4 cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 border=0>
  <TBODY>
  <TR>
    <TD height=4></TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE><SPAN class=t2>- Providing Customers and 
Investors Comprehensive Information About Global Diversified Industries, Its 
Achievements and Products -</SPAN> 
<P>
<DIV class=ar>CHOWCHILLA, Calif., June 16 /PRNewswire-FirstCall/ -- Global 
Diversified Industries, Inc. (OTC Bulletin Board: <A 
href="http://finance.yahoo.com/q?s=gdvi.ob&amp;d=t">GDVI</A> - <A 
href="http://www.zinester.com/lr/193009/4952643">News</A>), focused on the modular 
building industry with emphasis on the education market, has launched its new 
website at <A href="http://www.zinester.com/lr/193011/4952643">http://www.gdvi.net</A> to keep 
customers, shareholders and others interested in the Company up-to-date on its 
products, services, and accomplishments. 
<P>Key features for visitors to the website include sample modular building 
designs that visitors can use to design a custom building for their next 
project. Also included are links to current stock pricing, press releases and 
other pertinent public information about the Company, along with photographs of 
projects utilizing the Company's well-known, popular Aurora(TM) designs. 
<P>Global Diversified Industries Chairman and CEO Phil Hamilton said that "we 
have spent a considerable amount of time and effort on providing an informative, 
yet easily navigated website for both our customers and investors. As our core 
business continues to grow, we will update and modify our website to keep all 
visitors informed about and interested in all things about Global Diversified." 
<P>About Global Diversified Industries, Inc. 
<P>Global Diversified Industries, Inc. is a holding company with two 
wholly-owned subsidiaries, Global Modular, Inc. and MBS Construction, Inc. Both 
are engaged in the modular construction marketplace with an emphasis on 
educational projects. They incorporate the latest in construction software, 
allowing them to better manage projects incorporating cost vs. profit ratios, 
construction and manufacturing schedules, purchasing, receiving and other facets 
of industrial management. The Company's work is found in Northern and Southern 
California, with numerous projects on budget for school systems throughout the 
state. 
